or door in your office our 15+ years of signmaking have taught us a thing or two about how to install an office sign under each product option on our website you’ll be able to choose the mounting option that works best for your needs - and most are available at no added cost review the video on mounting options contact our team to inquire more or learn about each mounting option in the section below contact us double-sided foam tape our industrial-strenh double-sided foam tape creates a secure bond between your sign and mounting surface and is available in multiple thicknesses which our quality control department will automatically affix based on your sign’s size usage information: best to use on flat non-porous walls or doors purchase 3m clear tape glass tape this mounting option is easy-to-use provides high strenh and long-term durability and best of all will go undetected on the backside of your sign when installed on glass our 3m clear tape is the perfect sign mounting option for any window or glass installs usage information: best used on internal windows or glass surfaces purchase velcro this hook & loop velcro mounting tape is a good option to consider if you plan to routinely change out your signage for example if you have a sign on your wall that you routinely swap out for another sign velcro is a great solution for you usage information: best to use for low-bond easy-to-replace sign installs purchase 3m command strips this mounting option is arguably the easiest to install and the easiest to remove without tearing paint or damaging a wall or door similar to our velcro solution this mounting option also is a good one to consider for temporary or replaceable signage installs usage information: best used on painted stained or varnished wood or walls purchase magnetic mounting affixing your sign to a metal substrate wall or door magnetic tape is a great option for you this mounting option is available for several standard products or can be requested custom for any sign that you’d like to readily remove and reapply to walls and doors usage information: ensure that you will be mounting the sign to a door or wall with magnetic properties purchase cubicle fangs these metal sign fasteners are an ideal hanging and fastening device if your sign will be installed to a fabric substrate or cubicle cloth if you are looking to put employee nameplates on cubicles - you’ve found your ideal low-cost mounting option usage information: ensure that you will be using this on a fabric or cloth wall or partition purchase stand-offs stand-offs are a great mounting option for both interior and exterior signage they cover up screws used to affix a sign to a wall and provide a gap between the sign and the wall for a polished professional look easy to install & great for replacing signs and utilizing the same stand-offs for the new sign usage information: will require you to drill holes in your wall in order to mount purchase hanging cables
